        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and elsewhere. He abhors reproof, because it is a reproach to him, and because it strikes at the sin which he loves. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he that hateth reproof shall die — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, shall be destroyed, both here and for ever; which is a more grievous thing than a harsh reproof. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A scorner loveth not — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, hateth and avoideth; (more being understood than expressed;) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "one that reproveth him — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That tells him of his faults, warns him of his danger: and advises him to reform his conduct; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "neither will he go unto the wise — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That is, the godly: he will not seek their company and conversation, as his duty and interest oblige him to do, because he knows they will make conscience of reproving him.",
