  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 10.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Correction is grievous unto him that forsaketh the way.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The verse is climacteric, and the first clause is better translated, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "There is a grievous correction for him that forsaketh the way",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; then the second clause denotes what that correction is: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "he that hateth reproof",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " he that forsaketh the way - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "shall die.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"The way\" is the path of goodness and righteousness (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 2:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"The way of life.\" the Vulgate calls it; so ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 10:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Ecclesiastes 21:6, \"He that hateth reproof is in the way of sinners.\" The Authorized Version is quite allowable, and is supported in some degree by the Vulgate, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Doctrina mala deserenti viam vitae.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The sinner is annoyed by discipline, correction, or true teaching, because they curb the indulgence of his passions, make him uneasy in conscience, and force him to look to future issues. Septuagint, \"The instruction of the guileless (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἀκάκου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is known by passers-by; but they who hate reproofs die shamefully.\" The Syriac adopts the same rendering; but it is a question whether the word ought not to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "κακοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Menander says - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ὁ μὴ δαρεὶς ἄνθρωπος οὐ παιδεύεται",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
